Full Description: Citadels MC is an exclusive motorcycle club catering to dedicated and passionate riders who share a common bond. Our club consists of a diverse community, welcoming both active and retired members from law enforcement, military, first responders, as well as civilian motorcycle enthusiasts. We provide a platform for like-minded individuals to come together, form lifelong friendships, and engage in the exhilarating world of motorcycles. At Citadels MC, we understand the unique experiences and camaraderie that arise from serving in law enforcement, the military, and as first responders. We honor the dedication and sacrifice of our members, and our club serves as a place where they can find support, understanding, and a shared passion for motorcycles. Our club is not limited to professionals in uniform; we also embrace civilian motorcycle enthusiasts who possess a deep appreciation for the open road, two-wheeled machines, and the sense of freedom that comes with riding. Whether you are a seasoned rider or a novice, we welcome individuals from all walks of life who share a common love for motorcycles. As a member of Citadels MC, you gain access to a vibrant and active community that organizes regular rides, events, and gatherings. These experiences allow our members to forge strong bonds, exchange stories, and create memories that will last a lifetime. Our club fosters a sense of unity and belonging, providing a supportive network where riders can connect, share knowledge, and contribute to the broader motorcycle community. Join us today and become a part of a tight-knit community where friendship, adventure, and the love of motorcycles unite. Ride with purpose and ride with pride as a member of Citadels MC.

Description: Advanced antenna technology, customized to exceed customer needs.
Headquarters Regions: Great Lakes, Midwestern US
Full Description: The IINNTENNA is a next-generation antenna technology that is changing the global RF landscape and bringing telecommunications into the future. Our chief antenna scientist, Dr. Mohamed S. Sanad, changed the world’s telecommunications trajectory at Nokia in 1994, leading the invention of the first internally embedded mobile phone antennas. Hoping to change the problematic direction of antenna technology growing in size and weight without delivering more efficient signals, Dr. Sanad dedicated the past 15 years to create what we now know as the IINNTENNA- a smaller, cost effective, and monumentally more efficient antenna evolution. With decades of experience, a passion for revolutionary antenna advancement, and his innate concern for humanity at large, Dr. Sanad’s work has tackled even more problems than he initially intended to solve. This technology’s broadband, far-reaching capabilities are vast. In base station applications it eliminates the need for multiple towers in any given area, positively impacting the global landscape, minimizing deforestation, and significantly reducing exposure to radiation from the daily use of our wireless devices. In satellites the IINNTENNA immensely decreases the size and weight of the structure while maximizing efficiency, cost, functionality, and much more. The IINNTENNA’s features can be used with almost any technology, including all LTE, WiFi, and Bluetooth devices, which could lead to a positive chain reaction that will take us into a more health-conscious and environmentally friendly future for all technological advancement. With the wide-scale integration of this technology, we will also experience global impact with increased upload/download speeds, reduced SAR and PIM values in active antenna technologies, and worldwide connectivity extending to aircraft and space technology. Interested in learning more about how the next generation of antenna technology can be applied to your products and company? Contact us for a commitment-free consultation today.

Description: Open source distributed SQL query engine for running interactive and ETL queries against multiple data sources.
Headquarters Regions: San Francisco Bay Area, West Coast, Western US
Full Description: Trino (formerly PrestoSQL) is a tool designed to efficiently query vast amounts of data using distributed queries. If you work with terabytes or petabytes of data, you are likely using tools that interact with Hadoop and HDFS. Trino was designed as an alternative to tools that query HDFS using pipelines of MapReduce jobs, such as Hive or Pig, but Trino is not limited to accessing HDFS. Trino can be and has been extended to operate over different kinds of data sources, including traditional relational databases and other data sources such as Cassandra. Trino was designed to handle data warehousing and analytics: data analysis, aggregating large amounts of data and producing reports. These workloads are often classified as Online Analytical Processing (OLAP).
Founders: Dain Sundstrom, David Phillips, Martin Traverso

Description: Crely is developing a medical device-enabled clinical decision support platform to detect, predict and reduce surgical site infections.
Headquarters Regions: Greater Los Angeles Area, West Coast, Western US
Full Description: Surgical site infections (SSI), are a common complication following all types of surgery, and are thought to result from contamination occurring during the procedure. SSIs are the #1 cause of unplanned re-admissions after surgery. Around 60% of SSIs are detected after discharge from hospital, and a 45-hour delay in treatment of SSI increases odds by 3.8x of infection-related deaths. There is a huge unmet need for post-operative monitoring of the patient, and a credible and reliable early warning system for surgical site infections. Until now, clinicians have had to rely on actual physical observation of the surgical wound to determine if an infection is present. A major concern is that infection may be present but not show any outward clinical signs and thus would be missed. Additionally, there may be a significant time delay before the physician may be able to observe the wound. Crely is developing a medical device-enabled clinical decision support platform to detect, predict, manage, and reduce surgical site infections
